 	<div class="modal-body">
        	<div class="container-fluid text-center">
			<h2>A Riverside Date</h2>
			<h4>After waiting for two months and nineteen days,<br>
Finally he blessed me with, her reverent grace.<br>
She made me understood the paramountcy of time,<br>
Certainly that led us getting indulge in noblest crime.<br>
An orange Wednesday morning marked, ‘A Riverside Date’<br> 
Wearing Orange bliss sundress she was one to imitate.<br>
Kohl lined hazel eyes with gentle curls of hair,<br>
She was no lesser than the cover girl of ‘Vanity Fair’.<br>
Gentle Sea breeze kept pulsing her Red Cheeks,<br>
Like a maverick playing with emerald in calcite matrix.<br>
Her eyes ruled my ears with an acoustic melody of Gibson,<br>
Like an Eurasian ivy continuously being rained upon.<br>
Having her by my side always provided motivation,<br>
At that time I felt I am no longer an Utopian.<br>
Her rheumy eyes hankered me to drown<br>
To possess the two pearls of goddess crown.<br>
Although her nature was way too pedantic,<br>
But the romanticism between us too became gigantic.<br>
The dusk marked the end of a ‘A Riverside Date’,<br>
With our love determined to change our fate.<br>
<em><b>Mrigank Prasoon</b></em>
			</h4>
		</div>	
